ExLlamaV3 (the EXL3 format and codec)
    https://github.com/turboderp-org/exllamav3
    License: MIT

PonyExl3 reimplements the EXL3 quantization codec for Apple Silicon / Metal.
The following are direct ports of, or derived from, exllamav3 source:

  - ponyexl3/ref/{trellis,codebook,hadamard,perm,signs,reconstruct}.py
      CPU reference of the EXL3 trellis pack/unpack, 3INST procedural
      codebooks, blockwise Walsh–Hadamard transform, and permutation —
      ported from exllamav3_ext/quant/*.cu and the exllamav3 quant modules.
  - ponyexl3/mlx/* trellis-decode, sign/Hadamard, and MoE routing logic
      reimplemented in Metal kernels following the exllamav3 algorithms.
  - ponyexl3/reference/* export/compare tooling that calls the exllamav3
      Python API to produce cross-platform reference tensors.

